Turbo inlet pipe.. Makes a big difference

An aftermarket turbo inlet pipe is significantly bigger than the stock Vw part where the stock part is narrow going into the turbo many aftermarket ones are twice the size than stock.. So bigger pipe more air, more power.. Fast turbo spool.. Better throttle response.. They come in two types turbo elbow which replaces the stock plastic one either cast (like APR) or metal... or inlet pipe which is the elbow plus the pipe that connects to the airbox (like forge or turbo technics).. Cheap mod well worth it...
